"n. 义务，负担 【英】 n. 义务, 负担(a difficult, unpleasant task) 【记】 分割记忆：on－us， 在我们身上的'责任' 无 【记】源自onerous；on + us 在我们身上的→重担 onus (n.)  1640s, from Latin onus ""load, burden,"" figuratively ""tax, expense; trouble, difficulty,"" from PIE *en-es- ""burden"" (source of Sanskrit anah ""cart, wagon""). Hence legal Latin onus probandi (1722), literally ""burden of proving."""
